column4: Offers a solution (e.g. “What about those creates? Would they have something to do with the issue?”)
column6: Implies that they should resolve the situlation together rather than making a threat (e.g. "we may have to go to the higher officer if we don't get a solution" not "I will have to go to a higher officer")

column3: Dialogue

If you don't agree to help me, I'll have to speak with your commander. I've also noticed that you were pointing to the supply containers when you were talking to your commander, and I think this is a part of the problem.
If there's nothing he can do I would try to suggest that we talk to his commander together
What equipment are you lacking from your supply containers over there? Maybe we can work together on this.
I don't want to, but if you can't help me, I will have to talk with your commander. I noticed you pointing at the containers of supplies earlier. Is that the problem?

Commander, I understand your concerns, but I think it would be beneficial to both of our teams if we could cooperate and I'm certain your commander would feel the same way if I discussed this with him.  If supplies are your concern, let's formulate a plan to be sure both of our platoons are well equipped.
I'd like to solve this problem between the two of us. It is imperative  we work together on this. Do those supplies over there have anything to do with the issue at hand?
If you refuse to speak to my commander there will be a bad outcome
Is it possible to discuss everything between the two of us without going to a higher ranked officer? You can have confidence that we will try to do what's best with the limited supplies we have.
I will have to ask your commander about what is wrong with the supplies.

We really need your help on this one. If you can help us in this time of need, you will be repaid two-fold after our mission is complete. I don't want to have to go above you on this one, but we are truly desperate.
Chain of Command will be called if you do not cooperate with me on this issue.
Sir, my men really need your help in order to accomplish this mission. If you aren't willing sir, than with all due respect I will have to go to a higher-ranking officer.
My job is to make sure we have your help. I hope you and I can work this out, but if not, I will have to go above your head.
Your commander committed help and we will like to inform him that his words are being kept
I need to talk to your superior if you are not going to help. I noticed he was pointing towards the barrels, tell me is that the cause of the problem.
sir, if you refuse to help, i will be forced to speak with your commander. also, did you have any questions about the supplies?
I will be meeting with your commander later.
Hey, come over here for a second. Let's take a look at these supplies. Does everything look alright? Let's work this out without anyone else getting involved. What do you say?
I would like to speak with your commander about this

If you do not agree to help, I would then have to find your commander and talk to him which would be even more of a hassle. Furthermore, I noticed that you were pointing to that box of supplies over there. The plane that is carrying the equipment for you is delayed and that is why I need your help.

Captain, I have commitments here. I need to get an answer, if you do not have the authority to resolve this wth me, I need to go higher. I am simply asking out of courtesy, but will do what i need out of necessity.
Is there something I should know? I want to work with you but if I don't get any answers, I will go to your commander.

I WOULD TRY TO EXPLAIN TO HIM THAT IT IS IN HIS BEST INTEREST TO WORK WITH ME RATHER THAN AGAINST ME.  BUT THAT I WOULD DEFNITELY CONTACT HIS SUPERIOR IF THAT WAS NEEDED.  I WOULD ASK HIM WHAT I COULD DO TO HELP HIM BE ABLE TO HELP ME, SHOULD I CALL SOMEONE ABOUT THE SHIPMENT, SHOULD WE WAIT ON THE PLANES TO ARRIVE, COULD WE WORK SOMETHING OUT WITH THE SUPPLIES THAT THEY ALREADY HAD.  I WOULD TRY TO SHOW HIM THAT I WAS WILLING TO HELP OUT AND BE PART OF THE SOLUTION.  HOWEVER, IF HE STILL REFUSED, THEN I WOULD CONTACT THE NEXT HIGHER UP OFFICIAL THAT I NEEDED TO.
Is there any way you could help even though your equipment has not arrived?  I don't want to have to go over your head.  Is there something wrong with the supplies you were pointing to earlier?
Let's discuss the supplies you have pointed out and get this situation resolved so we don't have to escalate this problem to superiors.
Sir, I have to talk to your commander in charge if you cannot offer assistance. There is a miscommunication between parties and the supplies have been causing the problem.

Sir I would believe it would be in the best interest for us to resolve this issue among ourselves rather than having further delay with the mission we are trying to accomplish. I am sure that we are more than capable of resolving this between us

I noticed that when you were talking to your commander, you were pointing at the container of supplies. Does that have anything to do with why you say you can't help? If you refuse to help, I'm going to have to speak with your commander.

I understand your predicament and i would much rather us working out this situation together rather my having to approach your commander.  I notice you were looking at the supplies; is there any way i can be of assistance in helping you solve any issues you are having regarding those containers of supplies?
I think we need to work together to benefit these people in need,  and your superiors will appreciate your actions.

Judging from your conversation with your commander, I believe there has been some problems related to your teams supplies, so, i suggest you help me or else i have to talk to your commander about your coordination.

You need to understand the importance of this situation, and your help is imperative. I understand that you were talking to your commander about the containers of supplies, and I am wondering who I need to speak to make this happen. I would appreciate your help now, so that I do not need to investigate this any further.
Commander it is critial that get the team engaged to help. I need you to motivate your team a show that you are capable of solving this problem without going up the ranks.

Yes sir, I understand that it is out of your control so I will set up a meeting with your commander and mine to discuss supplies. But i would rather avoid getting the higher ups involved, so lets work this out at our level. Is there a work around for the equipment?

It would be in both of our best interest to deal with this among ourselves, I will have to talk to your commander otherwise which may not be best for you. Are the containers of supplies causing any delays?
I saw you pointing at the containers of supplies and wondered if this might have something to do with the problem; I'd like to bring the commander into this conversation.
If there is disagreement, I must speak to the commander.
Hey, let's get the stuff we have unloaded so we both look good for your boss.
I would call my higher ranked officer and explained to them the situation at hand and tell them that they have to call the Chinese army platoon higher ranked commander.
Unless you get your men down here to help with this equipment I am going to get my boss and trust me you dont want that to happen.  Now if we work together on this equipment we wont have any issues.
As an American soldier, you should ash your higher ranked officer for help, not try to asking the Chinese commander at first. Your officer will then ask the Chinese commander for help.
We need to find solutions for this important business connection. If you are not able to help me, I would like to speak to your direct supervisor so we can carry out this important deal.

I will informed my commanding officer first, wait for his command. If my commanding officer said that I can go ahead and talk to higher rank, I will do so. I will talk first to my counterpart that I was given the permission to talk to higher rank, with out most respect to his rank.
You really don't want me going to a higher ranked officer and I'm trying to prevent having to do so, but you need to work with me right now. What can we do to both get what we need in this situation?

Can we lend you any of our equipment so that you can proceed before your own supplies arrive?  You and I can work together to get this done.  We don't need to go through our superiors for so simple a decision.
If you won't help, I'll need to talk to your commander.
If you don't agree we will have to go to your commander again.
Surely it would be better for us to resolve this issue with the supplies between ourselves.and not have to involve your commander.
I will request him that it is better to cooperate than to make me go to a higher ranked officer.
Is your company in need of supplies?
We need to work together on this. We have enough supplies for all of us. It isn't good for me or you, but it's what needs to be done.
This isn't a good situation, and I realize the solution to the problem isn't perfect, but if we don't come to an agreement my hands are tied.
What are in those containers? Are they part of the issue here? We must come to a consensus, we can work this out.
Let's please compromise. There are more than enough supplies for both of us to achieve our objectives.
It's not a perfect solution, but unless we compromise between manning and supplies, we will have no other alternative.
I saw you indicating these containers. Is there a concern with them? We can resolve that, if necessary.
Let's work here. There is ample supply left. We can't do it to ruin our image.
I don't have any other available options so have to come to an agreement.
The containers over there, do you have an issue with those? We'll have to come to an agreement to work this out.
It looks bad but we have plenty of supplies here for everyone.
Its not what we wanted but we have no choice, we have to compromise.
We have to make this work. It your issue with the containers you were pointing at?
I would appreciate your continuing support. There are enough supplies and we should be able to work together to resolve the situation as quicky as possible.

I understand your concerns about the containers. In my personal opinion, cooperation would be the best solution. I am committing to make this work and would welcome any discussion and cooperation from you.
Pleas try to work with me here. There are plenty of supplies for everyone. I don't want to do it either as it reflects poorly on both of us.

It looks bad for both of us if we don't complete this. We have enough supplies. Let's work through this.
I know it's not ideal, but we have to come up with a solution.
Is there an issue with the containers? We have to find a way to make this work.
Please work with me. We have plenty of supplies and you and I both know it will make us look bad.

We need to come to a compromise with manning or supplies. I know its not an ideal situation but I will have no choice.
